                <note rend="inline" type="source">875.01/243: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Albania</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-06-24T13:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1924—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>39. Legation’s 56 of June 19 and 58 of June 21. Unless the head of the State has
                    been changed, the question of recognition does not seem to arise. There is no
                    objection to your continuing to carry on with the present Government the
                    relations which you had with the preceding one if in your opinion it is properly
                    constituted, stable, and in control of the country. You are authorized at your
                    discretion to continue such relations. Department desires telegraphic report of
                    your action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
